728015f-a.text:
Springfield Boulevard (formerly Rocky Hill Road), east side, between Seventy-third Ave. (formerly Black Stump Road, BlThk Road, and Cedar Lane), and Horace Harding Boulevard (formerly West Alley Road, Sixty-first Ave., and also Nassau Boulevard), showing an old unpainted farmhouse which was the residence of Thos. Valentine from 1873 to 1896. It was still standing in 1928. If standing in 1937, it would be on the east side of Springfield Boulevard between Sixty-seventh and Sixty-ninth Aves.
January 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

728016f-b.text:
Springfield Boulevard, west side, between 73rd and 75th Aves., showing in a set of four views a dilapidated house which housed C. Backus in 1860. In 1873 it was on the N.W. corner of Granger Ave. (now one) and Rocky Hill Road. In 1891, A. H. Richie controlled 250B acres in this area including this house and surrounding land.
January 1923.
Eumene L. Armbruster Collection.
